cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Fluid Dynamics: A Single-Axiom View of Navier-Stokes, Turbulence, Boundary Layers, Vortices, Magnetohydrodynamics, Astrophysical Flows, and the Clay Millennium Problem"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current latest
  Tier 0 v3.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to fluid dynamics. This is
  Tier 1 paper #23, the seventh paper of Block A (Physics/Math
  deepening), introducing K_flow = K_visc ⊕ K_turb ⊕ K_boundary ⊕
  K_compressible ⊕ K_vortex ⊕ K_MHD ⊕ K_astro ⊕ K_NS-regularity, and
  completing the EXTENDED MATTER BLOCK with Tier 1 #17 (K_geom, DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20230667), #19 (K_cosmic, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20233952),
  #20 (K_field, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20234703), #21 (K_stat, DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20237082), and #22 (K_solid, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20249191).
  The ITU polytope reaches 23 vertices with #17-#23 all attaining
  degree 22 (new maximum). Pass-1 progress: 166 of 220 phases (75.5%).
  Phase 159 establishes K_flow backbone: Euler 1755, Bernoulli 1738,
  Navier-Stokes 1822-1845. Reynolds Re = UL/ν spans 18 orders across
  16 systems (bacterium 3e-5 → solar convection 1.3e11). Stokes drag
  F = 6πμRv matches Einstein D = k_BT/(6πμR) of Phase 146.
  Hagen-Poiseuille Q ∝ R^4 verified to slope 4.000 exactly.
  Phase 160 demonstrates Kolmogorov 1941 turbulence universality:
  K41 -5/3 spectrum slope = -1.667 (theory exactly -5/3). Kolmogorov
  microscale η = (ν³/ε)^(1/4) spans μm (jet exhaust) to mm (deep
  ocean). η/L ∝ Re^(-3/4). She-Leveque (1994) intermittency:
  ζ_p < p/3 for p > 3. Kraichnan (1967) 2D inverse cascade.
  Phase 161 recovers Prandtl boundary layer (1904), resolving
  D'Alembert paradox. Blasius f''(0) = 0.3321 (Howarth-table 0.3320),
  η_99 = 4.925 (theory 5.0). Rankine-Hugoniot normal shock for Ma=2:
  p×4.5, ρ×2.67, T×1.69, Ma_2 = 0.577. Apollo re-entry Ma=37,
  RH-ideal T_shock ~ 60,000 K (real ~5-10 kK with chemistry).
  Phase 162 proves Kelvin (1869) and Helmholtz (1858) theorems.
  4-vortex 2D RK4 conserves total Γ. Strouhal St = 0.21 universal for
  Re∈[200, 200,000]; Tacoma Narrows 1940 f ~ 1.66 Hz. Rayleigh-Bénard
  Ra_c = 1708. 3D vortex stretching ω(t) ∝ exp(γt) cascade engine.
  Quantum vortex Γ = h/m_He4 = 9.98×10⁻⁸ m²/s (Onsager 1949, Feynman
  1955). BEC Rb-87 @ 100Hz: vortex density 2.74e11/m², spacing 1.91 μm.
  Topological-quanta family: Φ_0 = h/(2e) (Phase 153 SC) ↔ Γ = h/m
  (SF).
  Phase 163 develops MHD: magnetic Reynolds R_m spans 13 orders (lab
  Hg 0.013 → AGN 1.3e13). Alfvén v_A across 8 cosmic plasmas
  (photosphere 8.9 km/s → magnetar > c). Magnetic pressure: ITER 110
  atm, magnetar 4e22 atm ≈ neutron star degeneracy scale (Phase 144).
  Plasma β: tokamak core 0.005 → photosphere granule 20.8.
  Solar wind 450 km/s, mass loss 3.3e16 kg/yr; Earth magnetopause
  7.7 R_E. ITER tokamak: nτ_E T = 5.55e21 keV·s/m³ = 1.85× Lawson
  threshold (Q=10 target).
  Phase 164 covers astrophysical fluids: Eddington L_Edd =
  1.26e31 (M/M_sun) W. Bondi accretion; Sgr A* overestimate 10⁵×
  observed (RIAF). Shakura-Sunyaev α-disk; Kerr extreme η = 1 - 1/√3
  = 0.423 (Thorne 1974) = 50× nuclear fusion. M87 shadow 19.9 μas,
  Sgr A* 26.7 μas (EHT 2019/2022 ✓, Phase 122). Doppler boost δ^4 at
  Γ=100 = 1.6e9 (blazar). Superluminal v_app = 9.95 c at Γ=10.
  Blandford-Znajek (1977) jet launching. Sedov-Taylor blast wave:
  Crab @ 1000 yr → 5.32 pc (observed ~5 pc ✓). Fermi (1949) shock
  acceleration → cosmic-ray E^(-2).
  Phase 165 presents Clay Millennium Navier-Stokes problem (2000,
  $1M, unresolved). 2D NS solved by Ladyzhenskaya (1969): vorticity
  bounded by Maximum Principle. 3D NS open: vortex stretching
  candidate. Leray (1934) weak solutions global existence;
  uniqueness/smoothness open. Serrin-Prodi (1959-1962) 2/q + 3/p ≤ 1;
  L³ endpoint (Iskauriaza 2003). Beale-Kato-Majda (1984): blow-up
  ⇔ ∫||ω||_L∞ dt = ∞. CKN (1982): singular set 1D parabolic measure 0.
  Tao (2014-2016): averaged-NS blow-up + scale-invariance barrier.
  Onsager (1949) Hölder 1/3 threshold proved by Isett (2018):
  α > 1/3 conserves energy, α < 1/3 dissipative — Fourier dual of
  K41 -5/3 spectrum (Phase 160 ✓).
  Phase 166 integrates under K_flow. 23-vertex polytope: 195 edges,
  ⟨k⟩=16.96, #17-#23 all degree 22 (new max). #23 strong couplings:
  #2 Plasma (0.95), #13 Climate (0.90), #21 Stat Mech (0.90), #22 CM
  (0.85), #18 BH (0.80), #10 Energy (0.80); avg 0.618. EXTENDED
  MATTER BLOCK K_geom + K_cosmic + K_field + K_stat + K_solid +
  K_flow covers physics in 6 K-states. Ten predictions for 2026-2050:
  NS Millennium 2050 P=0.30, DNS Re_λ>10000 2030 P=0.85, riblets
  2030 P=0.70, AI flow control 2035 P=0.65, hypersonic Mach 5 2035
  P=0.55, ITER Q>1 2028 P=0.85, M87 jet 2030 P=0.65, corona heating
  2030 P=0.70, sonic BH Hawking 2032 P=0.50, quantum vortex tangle
  2028 P=0.75. Grand P_avg = 0.650. Strong/Medium/Weak = 5/4/1.
  Central thesis: ITU axiom dS = d<K> specializes to K_flow for
  continuum velocity-field physics, unifying NS, turbulence, boundary
  layers, vortices, MHD, astrophysics, and the Clay Millennium
  Problem under one principle. EXTENDED MATTER BLOCK
  (#17+#19+#20+#21+#22+#23) covers physics in 6 K-states. Pass-1
  interpretive synthesis; numerical results agree with established
  literature.
